               <p>WILLIAM DAVIES. I am a <rs id="t18260622-173-viclabel867" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-173-victim985 t18260622-173-viclabel867"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18260622-173-crimeloc868">Chiswell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-173-crimeloc868" type="placeName" value="Chiswell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-173-crimeloc868" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-173-off865 t18260622-173-crimeloc868"></join>. On the 22d of May the prisoner came to my shop alone; I saw her standing against the counter, at the further end of the shop, near to a lady, who was buying a shawl; I asked what she wanted - she showed me a very ancient pattern of print, and asked if I could match it; I saw she had something under her arm; I kept the pattern some time, and moved about, and then said I had not got the pattern; she left the shop - I followed, and brought her back - she dropped this shawl, and I detained her.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260622-173-person986">
